This isn't about a fragging, per se, but is a story which includes a fragmentation grenade.<br><br>
When I landed my rear echelon job, the fellow I was replacing and I went to an EM club which wasn't the one we always went to. It was somewhere near the Division HQ, if I recall. It was on Post.<br><br>
We were sitting there, having a drink, when all of a sudden a blast right outside blew in a plate glass window - glass flying everywhere. We watched stunned as everyone rose to their feet and headed for the door. <br><br>
The old, grizzled sarge I was with recommended we stay inside. So he and I got our drinks and ducked under the table. Kinda made sense - as danger in the form of another grenade could have been waiting outside.<br><br>
Never could figure out what the f*** was going on - just thought that it may have been a disgruntled patron.<br><br>
One wasn't safe anywhere, anytime in that damned place.
